---@class AbstractBus : ComponentProxy This card allows for interfacing with [Stargate Tech 2](http://stargatetech.theender.net/miscellaneous/home.html "http://stargatetech.theender.net/miscellaneous/home.html")'s Abstract Bus system.<br/>The abstract bus generates a signal named `bus_message` if a message is received. See the [signals reference](https://ocdoc.cil.li/component:signals "component:signals").
---@field getEnabled fun():boolean Returns whether the local bus interface is enabled.
---@field setEnabled fun(enabled:boolean) Sets whether the local bus interface should be enabled
---@field getAddress fun():number Returns the local interface address. number is a 16 bit hexadecimal number (0xFFFF being a broadcast). Returns 0 if an address has not yet been set.
---@field setAddress fun(address: number) Sets the local interface address. number is a 16bit hexadecimal number.
---@field scan fun(mask:number):table Scans the abstract bus for attached devices and returns them in a list.
---@field send fun(address:number,data:table):boolean Sends data across the abstract bus. The table `data` is in the form of key-value pairs, e.g.<br/>`lua> component.abstract_bus.send(0xFFFF, { ["action"]="dial", ["address"]="Losomdeh Salothirt Erpac" })`<br/><br/>-   See SGTech2 documentation for more info on the Abstract Bus.